here is the steps how you do the answer for question number 3
1. go to your server page by"ssh your_username@your_server_ip_address"
2. long list the file you will get .ssh directory
3. cd in to .ssh
4. long list the file in .ssh directory using ls -ls command
5. you will see a file named authorized_keys
6. open it using any editor like vi or vim
7. now, the file contains two keys that is one is akey ending with ...alx_applicant_server
and the other key is your public key
now append the given public key at the end of the file 
n.b dont delete any of those key
finally save change the file permision of authorized_keys to 600 and .ssh dir to 700
now it will work you can check your checker
